 a reverse Taunt</span><hr size=1> I've partnered with a number of young rouges, many who are still learning to sneak and hide reliably.  While grouped or not, you can practice your pickpocket skill by stopping your attack briefly and then try to steal.  You'll find that goblins, orcs and gnolls work well, since they usually have a few coppers in their pockets to take.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Evade</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> works on a similar principle, you can't hide while attacking, but you can attempt to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> duck</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> out of combat, if stop swinging for a moment.  <br>
{effect-to lower your rouge's hate on the MOB's aggro list}.<br>
<br>
Some experienced players use a hotkey to do both things.<br>
<br>
You'll find that most groups would prefer you don't steal from the party and refrain using pickpocket.  I usually asure them that it isn't a problem, by occasionally /split a handful of gold or even platinum.  Coppers and silvers are usually chump change and many avoid being encumbered and will drop it anyways.  One other role you can request is master looter ('cept noDrop).  The loot junk no one really wants, I'll go sell at the end and /split back about 75% to the group.  Everyone likes to here kaChing and a few may ask &quot;what was that for?&quot;.<br>
<br>
